The paper discusses the application of causal inference models in machine learning, specifically in the areas of economics, healthcare, and marketing. This suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.ML) or data science (cs.DS). The paper also introduces a novel approach that draws upon bandit literature, indicating that it may also fall under the sub-category of computational economics (cs.CE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CE, followed by cs.ML and cs.DS.
